post_text:
Food Distribution will begin, Tomorrow, Wednesday, September 9th.

‚Ä¢ Food will be brought to your home address on file each Wednesday during Distance Learning (when school is in session).

‚Ä¢ Someone must be present at the time of drop off in order to receive a food bag. Bags will not be left unattended.

‚Ä¢ Food drops will include 5 breakfast and 5 lunch meals for each of your children.

‚Ä¢ Buses will leave the school at 10:00 on Wednesdays to distribute the food.

‚Ä¢ Each Wednesday, you will receive a phone call (from a non-Stonebridge number) shortly before your food arrives.

‚Ä¢ All families will receive the food drop the first week. If you choose to opt out after the first week you must fill out a form declining your participation in the food program.

‚Ä¢ Families who miss their food drop can come to the school between 1-3pm to pick up their bag.

Minnesota Department of Human Services
July 28 at 4:09 PM ¬∑

üçéüçé Apply by Friday, July 31, for P-EBT üçéüçé

Tens of thousands of children could miss out on healthy food if their families don‚Äôt apply for Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer, also referred to as P-EBT, benefits by July 31. Minnesota school children who qualify for the federal free and reduced-price meal program are eligible to receive $325 per child with an additional $100 per child for Summer P-EBT.

Twenty counties have particularly low participation rates, where the families of 31-52% of eligible children have not yet applied.

Families who have already applied do not need to reapply. For information on when to expect benefits, see mn.gov/dhs/p-ebt/faqs/.

For more information, see the news release that includes a map showing counties with the largest percentage of children still eligible for P-EBT: http://mn.gov/dhs/media/news/index.jsp?id=1053-441837

post_text:
Update on Face Coverings and Requirements under Executive Order 20-81:

As of July 25, 2020, per the Governor‚Äôs Executive Order 20-81, people in Minnesota are required to wear a face covering in all public indoor spaces.

Effective Saturday, July 25, 2020 All Stonebridge students in grades K-8, staff, and other people present in the school building or riding on school transportation (this includes buses and vans) are required to wear a face covering. Face coverings will be required in all public areas within the school.

The covering should cover the nose and mouth completely, should not be overly tight or restrictive, and should feel comfortable to wear.

We appreciate your cooperation!

Minnesota Department of Human Services
June 30 at 11:21 AM ¬∑

The deadline to apply for pandemic food benefits (P-EBT) has been extended to July 31. DHS and the Minnesota Department of Education urge families with school children ‚Äì now including those in a school district pre-K program ‚Äì who received free and reduced-price meals to apply online at www.mn.p-ebt.org. Up to 150,000 eligible families have not yet applied.

P-EBT benefits are issued in a lump sum of $325 per child. Also, an additional $100 per child will be issued in August to all families eligible for P-EBT. More information is in a news release:
http://mn.gov/dhs/media/news/index.jsp?id=1053-438572

#StaySafeMN

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit
Transfer

What is P-EBT?
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a temporary food benefit available to Minnesota families with children who would have received free or reduced-price meals if schools were open. Families with eligible children will receive a one-time payment of $325 per child on a new or existing EBT card to help fill the gap created by a loss of school meals. The U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) has authorized the Minnesota Department of Human Services, the Minnesota Department of Education and Code for America to operate the program.

Stonebridge World School
May 29 at 12:09 PM ¬∑

Just a reminder that these meetings will be happening again today! Students, please join if you would like. Meeting links are located on Bloomz and google classrooms.

Stonebridge Family,

We know that the horrific death of George Floyd as well as the subsequent fires and destruction are impacting our students. We will be offering an ongoing open zoom call, starting today, facilitated by our support staff during the following times.

Middle School: 1:00pm-2:00pm

3rd - 5th grade : 2:05-3:00pm

PreK- 2nd : 3:05pm-4:00pm

This will be a space for students to express their feelings about the recent events and receive support from peers and staff. Please encourage your child to join if you feel like they would benefit.

These meeting will be held today, tomorrow and Monday.

Please check on Bloomz or Google Classroom for the Zoom link.

Peanut butter, bread, cold cuts, sliced cheese, crackers, canned soup or stew, canned fruit, canned vegetables, canned fish, canned beans, pasta and sauce, rice, toilet paper.

noon-2pm Today
Meet at Sanctuary Church, 710 West Broadway Ave, Minneapolis 55411

Just a reminder that these meetings will be happening again today! Students, please join if you would like. Meeting links are located on Bloomz and google classrooms.

Stonebridge Family,

We know that the horrific death of George Floyd as well as the subsequent fires and destruction are impacting our students. We will be offering an ongoing open zoom call, starting today, facilitated by our support staff during the following times.

Middle School: 1:00pm-2:00pm

3rd - 5th grade : 2:05-3:00pm

PreK- 2nd : 3:05pm-4:00pm

This will be a space for students to express their feelings about the recent events and receive support from peers and staff. Please encourage your child to join if you feel like they would benefit.

These meeting will be held today, tomorrow and Monday.

Please check on Bloomz or Google Classroom for the Zoom link.

Food Assistance Reminder:

CAPHC | Hennepin County SNAP Information

The Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP), formerly known as Food Support or Food Stamps, helps individuals and families afford the cost of food at grocery stores and farmer's markets. The program is designed to supplement a family or individual's income by providing money that can be spent on food.

https://www.caphennepin.org/services/food-support/supplemental-nutrition-assistance-program-snap-food-support/

Important Information

Tenant rights during COVID-19: Governor Walz just extended the "peacetime state of emergency" in MN until June 12th. This means that landlords are not allowed to evict tenants during this period. According to Legal Aid, as long as we're in a statewide peacetime emergency, renters can't be evicted unless landlords prove they have "endangered the health and safety of other residents"

so that we can hold a spot for your child or children. If you don‚Äôt know for sure, you can put ‚Äúmaybe‚Äù on the survey.

Remember, we are here if you need anything. Call the school or send an email to any staff member. You can find our staff directory on our webpage.

Please Read:
Last week, Governor Tim Walz announced that all public PreK-12 schools in Minnesota will continue Distance Learning through the end of the 2019-2020 school year. As part of this Executive order, Stonebridge must use Friday May 1, and Monday, May 4 to plan for the continuation of Distance Learning for the rest of the school year.

This means that students will not have classes on May 1 or May 4. Please use this time to complete any missing work or to enjoy some sunshine.

If you have not completed our Distance Learning survey, we would love it if you take a few minutes to give us some feedback on how things are going. Click on the link to complete the short survey. https://forms.gle/RjSEsc4qsqm6GBPh6

post_text:
Stonebridge World School Families,
Everyone at Stonebridge hopes you and your family are doing as well as you can be during this uncertain time. Today, Governor Tim Walz and the Minnesota Department of Education announced that all Public PreK-12 schools in Minnesota will continue Distance Learning through the end of the 2019-2020 school year. This means that students and school staff will not return to schools for the rest of the academic year.

If you need assistance accessing Distance Learning, please make sure you contact your child‚Äôs teacher: http://www.stonebridgeworldschool.org/teacher-schedules/

Meal Service
Stonebridge will continue to deliver meals every Monday.

Other Resources
Please make sure you are accessing our webpage for a list of other resources that are available at this time: http://www.stonebridgeworldschool.org/

Please know that we are working hard to continue supporting our students academically, socially and emotionally during this time and that we MISS YOU ALL so very much!!

post_text:
A MESSAGE FROM STONEBRIDGE WORLD SCHOOL 3/15/20

Dear Stonebridge Families,

Governor Tim Walz has ordered schools to close by Wednesday, March 18 to reduce the spread of COVID-19.

Stonebridge World School will be OPEN for school on Monday, March 16th and Buses will run their regular scheduled routes this day. This will help staff and families prepare. Stonebridge will be CLOSED on Tuesday, March 17. At this time, classes are scheduled to resume Monday, April 6th after our spring break.

We will provide more info about learning alternatives, food supports, and other resources as we process guidance from the MN Department of Education. Please make sure you update your current contact information with our school office (612-877-7400) as soon as possible.

If you choose to keep your child home on Monday, please call the school attendance line at 612-877-7498 and leave a message so the absence can be marked as excused.

Thank you!

We will provide more info about learning alternatives, food supports, and other resources as we process guidance from the MN Department of Education. Please make sure you update your current contact information with our school office (612-877-7400) as soon as possible.

If you choose to keep your child home on Monday, please call the school attendance line at 612-877-7498 and leave a message so the absence can be marked as excused.

Thank you!

post_text:
It is with great sadness that we share that one our Stonebridge students was hit by a car Friday afternoon while crossing the street after exiting the school bus.

We are committed to doing all we can to support Stonebridge students, families and staff during this time. A support team is at Stonebridge today to provide counseling and support for any students or staff who need to talk with them.

This dear student is in our thoughts and prayers, as is her family. The Stonebridge community stands ready to do what we can to support the family, our students and staff.

A staff from Stonebridge has started to raise money to support the family during this time.

Please consider donating to help: https://www.facebook.com/donate/297903014493667/10101529359704540/
